.TH "tomoyo_check_inet_address" 9 "tomoyo_check_inet_address" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tomoyo_check_inet_address \- Check permission for inet domain socket's operation.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tomoyo_check_inet_address
.BI "(const struct sockaddr *addr "  ","
.BI "const unsigned int addr_len "  ","
.BI "const u16 port "  ","
.BI "struct tomoyo_addr_info *address "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
Pointer to "struct sockaddr".
.IP "addr_len" 12
Size of \fIaddr\fP.
.IP "port" 12
Port number.
.IP "address" 12
Pointer to "struct tomoyo_addr_info".
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on success, negative value otherwise.
